During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed a variety of topics including the commemoration of Martin Luther King Jr., President Trump's upcoming trip to West Virginia, the visit of the U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Teams to the White House, the administration's strategy to confront illegal immigration, and the potential deployment of the National Guard to the southern border. She also addressed questions regarding the ongoing investigation into Russian interference in the 2016 election, the potential for a trade dispute with China, the President's criticism of Amazon, and the future of the DACA program. Additionally, Sanders mentioned that the administration is reviewing the situation regarding EPA Administrator Scott Pruitt and his rental agreement with a lobbyist.